external_knowledge:
- 'Blooming' refers to achieving a high standard or performing well;
- 'Province of Ontario' is a specific geographical and administrative region in Canada;
- 'Average score higher than 70' indicates that the schools have performed above a certain threshold in their assessments.

- "top three students" refers to the highest scores for each student, ranked by their score value;
- "outperformed the average score" means the student's score is above the average score value of all assessments;
- "higher standard deviation" indicates that the variability in the student's scores is greater than the average variability across all assessments.

- "stand tall" refers to schools with an average class size greater than the overall average class size;
- "vast garden of education" is a metaphor for the educational system;
- "general growth of the forest" represents the overall average class size across all schools;
- "bloomed with actual class data" means schools that have class data.

- "Total enrollment" refers to the sum of students enrolled in all schools within a province;
- "Provinces with a total enrollment over 1000" means the sum of enrollments in all schools within a province exceeds 1000;
- "Schools with more than 1000 students" means the individual school has an enrollment greater than 1000.

- "shone the brightest" refers to the highest average scores;
- The year of assessment is 2019;
- "top 3 schools" means the schools ranked 1st, 2nd, and 3rd in each province.

- "shining star" refers to the top-performing province;
- "boasts the highest average score percentage" means the province has the highest average score when scores are normalized to a percentage of the maximum possible score;
- "assessments conducted in 2019 for type 0" specifies the year and type of the assessments considered.

sql:
SELECT AVG(score_value) 
FROM assessment_scores 
WHERE type_id = (SELECT type_id FROM assessment_types WHERE type_name = 'Standardized Test');

